entries.title: Three dead as New Zealand city faces ‘unprecedented’ flooding
entries.description: New Zealand’s Prime Minister Chris Hipkins said Auckland, the country's largest city, experienced its “wettest day on record,” receiving 75% of its usual summer rainfall in just 15 hours.

entries.title: 2 wounded in new Jerusalem attack, Israeli paramedics say
entries.description: A Palestinian gunman opened fire in east Jerusalem on Saturday, wounding at least two people, less than a day after another assailant killed seven outside a synagogue in the deadliest attack in the city since 2008.

entries.title: Japan launches whale meat vending machines to promote sales
entries.description: A Japanese whaling operator, after struggling for years to promote its controversial products, has found a new way to cultivate clientele and bolster sales: whale meat vending machines.

entries.title: 3 dead, 1 missing as rain pounds New Zealand’s largest city
entries.description: Authorities said Saturday that three people had died and at least one was missing after record levels of rainfall pounded New Zealand’s largest city, causing widespread disruption.

entries.title: At least seven people shot dead near Jerusalem synagogue
entries.description: At least seven people were shot dead near a synagogue in east Jerusalem today, Israeli police said, as violence escalated following a raid in the occupied West Bank city of Jenin. NBC News’ Meagan Fitzgerald has the latest.
